HEADWORD: Llandeilo group
<hw>Llan*dei"lo group`</hw>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A series of strata
in the lower Silurian formations of Great Britain; -- so named from
<ets>Llandeilo</ets> in Southern Wales. See <xex>Chart</xex> of
<er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Llanero</ent>⟦br⟧
